**********************************************************************************
* The netlist describes our monitoring scheme to detect the occurrence
* of faults and aging conditions affecting hardware blocks implementing an
* Othogonal Latin Squares (OLS) Double Error Correction (DEC) ECC.
* The netlist also implements the Encoder and Decoder blocks of a case study
* OLS DEC ECC with 16 information bits and 16 check bits.
**********************************************************************************


****************************************************************************
* Definition of parameters with CMOS transistor sizes
****************************************************************************
.PARAM wp='2*16n'
.PARAM lp=16n
.PARAM lpc='2*lp'
.PARAM wn=16n
.PARAM ln=16n
.PARAM lnc='2*ln'

****************************************************************************
* Definition of parameters for waveforms
****************************************************************************
.PARAM fclk=3.5G
.PARAM clk='1/fclk'
.PARAM trise=10ps
.PARAM tfall=10ps
.PARAM tset=15p
.PARAM tgb=30p
.PARAM tm='tset+tgb'
.Param tdelaynot = 12ps

****************************************************************************
* Definition of subcircuits of some needed elementary logic gates
****************************************************************************

.SUBCKT INV vdd vss in out
MP1 out in vdd vdd CMOSP W='wp*2' L=lp
MN1 out in vss vss CMOSN W='wn*2' L=ln
.ENDS

.SUBCKT INVx10 vdd vss in out
MP1 out in vdd vdd CMOSP W='wp*10' L=lp
MN1 out in vss vss CMOSN W='wn*10' L=ln
.ENDS

.SUBCKT XOR vdd vss in1 in2 out
XINV1 vdd vss in1 in1N INV
XINV2 vdd vss in2 in2N INV
MP1 nodeP in1N vdd vdd CMOSP W='wp*2' L=lp
MP2 nodeQ in1 vdd vdd CMOSP W='wp*2' L=lp
MP3 out in2 nodeP vdd CMOSP W='wp*2' L=lp
MP4 out in2N nodeQ vdd CMOSP W='wp*2' L=lp
MN1 out in1 nodeR vss CMOSN W='wn*2' L=ln
MN2 out in1N nodeS vss CMOSN W='wn*2' L=ln
MN3 nodeR in2 vss vss CMOSN W='wn*2' L=ln
MN4 nodeS in2N vss vss CMOSN W='wn*2' L=ln
.ENDS

.SUBCKT NAND vdd vss in1 in2 out
MP1 out in1 vdd vdd CMOSP W='wp*1' L=lp
MP2 out in2 vdd vdd CMOSP W='wp*1' L=lp
MN1 out in1 nodeN vss CMOSN W='wn*2' L=ln
MN2 nodeN in2 vss vss CMOSN W='wn*2' L=ln
.ENDS

.SUBCKT AND vdd vss in1 in2 out
XNAND vdd vss in1 in2 outNand NAND
XINV vdd vss outNand out INV
.ENDS

.SUBCKT NAND3 vdd vss in1 in2 in3 out
MP1 out in1 vdd vdd CMOSP W='wp*1' L=lp
MP2 out in2 vdd vdd CMOSP W='wp*1' L=lp
MP3 out in3 vdd vdd CMOSP W='wp*1' L=lp
MN1 out in1 nodeN1 vss CMOSN W='wn*3' L=ln
MN2 nodeN1 in2 nodeN2 vss CMOSN W='wn*3' L=ln
MN3 nodeN2 in3 vss vss CMOSN W='wn*3' L=ln
.ENDS

.SUBCKT AND3 vdd vss in1 in2 in3 out
XNAND3 vdd vss in1 in2 in3 outNand3 NAND3
XINV vdd vss outNand3 out INV
.ENDS

.SUBCKT NOR2 vdd vss in1 in2 out
MP1 nodeP in1 vdd vdd CMOSP W='wp*2' L=lp
MP2 out in2 nodeP vdd CMOSP W='wp*2' L=lp
MN1 out in1 vss vss CMOSN W='wn*1' L=ln
MN2 out in2 vss vss CMOSN W='wn*1' L=ln
.ENDS

.SUBCKT NOR4 vdd vss in1 in2 in3 in4 out
MP1 nodeP in1 vdd vdd CMOSP W='wp*4' L=lp
MP2 nodeQ in2 nodeP vdd CMOSP W='wp*4' L=lp
MP3 nodeR in3 nodeQ vdd CMOSP W='wp*4' L=lp
MP4 out in4 nodeR vdd CMOSP W='wp*4 ' L=lp
MN1 out in1 vss vss CMOSN W='wn*1' L=ln
MN2 out in2 vss vss CMOSN W='wn*1' L=ln
MN3 out in3 vss vss CMOSN W='wn*1' L=ln
MN4 out in4 vss vss CMOSN W='wn*1' L=ln
.ENDS

.SUBCKT OR4 vdd vss in1 in2 in3 in4 out
XNOR4 vdd vss in1 in2 in3 in4 outNor4 NOR4
XINV vdd vss outNor4 out INV
.ENDS

.SUBCKT NOTxCHAIN vdd vss in out
MP1 out in vdd vdd CMOSP W=Wp L=lpc
MN1 out in vss vss CMOSN W=Wn L=lnc
.ENDs

.SUBCKT NOTx1 vdd vss in out
MP1 out in vdd vdd CMOSP W=Wp L=lp
MN1 out in vss vss CMOSN W=Wn L=ln
.ENDs

.SUBCKT C2NOTx1 vdd vss Gp Gn in out
MP1 int1 Gp vdd vdd CMOSP W='1*Wp' L=lp
MP2 out in int1 Vdd CMOSP W='1*Wp' L=lp
MN1 out in int2 vss CMOSN W='1*Wn' L=ln
MN2 int2 Gn vss vss CMOSN W='1*Wn' L=ln
.ENDs


****************************************************************************
* Definition of subcircuits for the Encoder/Decoder
****************************************************************************
.SUBCKT XORCB vdd vss in1 in2 in3 in4 out
XXOR1 vdd vss in1 in2 out1 XOR
XXOR2 vdd vss in3 in4 out2 XOR
XXOR3 vdd vss out1 out2 out XOR
.ENDS

.SUBCKT MAJVOT vdd vss in1 in2 in3 in4 out
XAND3_1 vdd vss in1 in2 in3 out1 AND3
XAND3_2 vdd vss in2 in1 in4 out2 AND3
XAND3_3 vdd vss in3 in4 in1 out3 AND3
XAND3_4 vdd vss in4 in3 in2 out4 AND3
XOR4 vdd vss out1 out2 out3 out4 out OR4
.ENDS

.SUBCKT ErrDet vdd vss S0 S1 S2 S3 S4 S5 S6 S7 S8 S9 S10 S11 S12 S13 S14 S15 out
X_OR41 vdd vss S0 S1 S2 S3 int1 OR4
X_OR42 vdd vss S4 S5 S6 S7 int2 OR4
X_OR43 vdd vss S8 S9 S10 S11 int3 OR4
X_OR44 vdd vss S12 S13 S14 S15 int4 OR4
X_OR45 vdd vss int1 int2 int3 int4 out OR4
.ENDS


****************************************************************************
* Definition of subcircuit used to implement our proposed
* Fault anf Aging Detectors
****************************************************************************

****************************************************************************
* Buffer
****************************************************************************
.SUBCKT BUFF vdd vss in out
XINV1 vdd vss in outN INV
XINV2 vdd vss outN out INV
.ENDS

****************************************************************************
* Transmission gate
****************************************************************************
.SUBCKT TG vdd vss in clk clkn out
MP1 out clkn in vdd CMOSP W='wp' L=lp
MN1 out clk in vss CMOSN W='wn' L=ln
.ENDS

****************************************************************************
* Transition detector
****************************************************************************
.SUBCKT TD vdd vss in TWC TWCn out1 out2
XINV1 vdd vss in C NOTxCHAIN
*XINV2 vdd vss i1 i2 NOTxCHAIN
*XINV3 vdd vss i2 C NOTxCHAIN
XBUFF1 vdd vss C Cb BUFF
XTG1 vdd vss Cb TWC TWCn out1 TG
XTG2 vdd vss in TWC TWCn out2 TG
.ENDS

****************************************************************************
* 2-variable Two-Rail Checker (TRC)
****************************************************************************
.SUBCKT TRC2 vdd vss x1 y1 x2 y2 z1 z2
XAND2_1 vdd vss x1 y2 outAnd1 AND
XAND2_2 vdd vss x2 y1 outAnd2 AND
XAND2_3 vdd vss x1 x2 outAnd3 AND
XAND2_4 vdd vss y1 y2 outAnd4 AND
XNOR2_1 vdd vss outAnd1 outAnd2 z1 NOR2
XNOR2_2 vdd vss outAnd3 outAnd4 z2 NOR2
.ENDS

****************************************************************************
* 4-variable TRC
****************************************************************************
.SUBCKT TRC4 vdd vss x1 y1 x2 y2 x3 y3 x4 y4 z1 z2
XTRC2_1 vdd vss x1 y1 x2 y2 out1Trc1 out2Trc1 TRC2
XTRC2_2 vdd vss x3 y3 x4 y4 out1Trc2 out2Trc2 TRC2
XTRC2_3 vdd vss out1Trc1 out2Trc1 out1Trc2 out2Trc2 z1 z2 TRC2
.ENDS

****************************************************************************
* 6-variable TRC
****************************************************************************
.SUBCKT TRC6 vdd vss x1 y1 x2 y2 x3 y3 x4 y4 x5 y5 x6 y6 z1 z2
XTRC2_1 vdd vss x1 y1 x2 y2 out1Trc1 out2Trc1 TRC2
XTRC2_2 vdd vss x3 y3 x4 y4 out1Trc2 out2Trc2 TRC2
XTRC2_3 vdd vss x5 y5 x6 y6 out1Trc3 out2Trc3 TRC2
XTRC2_4 vdd vss out1Trc1 out2Trc1 out1Trc2 out2Trc2 out1Trc4 out2Trc4 TRC2
XTRC2_5 vdd vss out1Trc3 out2Trc3 out1Trc4 out2Trc4 z1 z2 TRC2
.ENDS

****************************************************************************
* 8-variable TRC
****************************************************************************
.SUBCKT TRC8 vdd vss x1 y1 x2 y2 x3 y3 x4 y4 x5 y5 x6 y6 x7 y7 x8 y8 z1 z2
XTRC4_1 vdd vss x1 y1 x2 y2 x3 y3 x4 y4 out1Trc1 out2Trc1 TRC4
XTRC4_2 vdd vss x5 y5 x6 y6 x7 y7 x8 y8 out1Trc2 out2Trc2 TRC4
XTRC2_1 vdd vss out1Trc1 out2Trc1 out1Trc2 out2Trc2 z1 z2 TRC2
.ENDS



****************************************************************************
* Generation of information bits (de0, ..., de15), that should be stored on the cache,
* and that are given as inputs to the Encoder block.
* These bits have been obtained by inverting signals (de0i, ..., de15i) gerenated by ideal
* voltage sources, so that these signal present realistic waveforms.
****************************************************************************
*Information bits (de0, ..., de15)
XVde0 vdd vss de0i de0 INVx10
XVde1 vdd vss de1i de1 INVx10
XVde2 vdd vss de2i de2 INVx10
XVde3 vdd vss de3i de3 INVx10
XVde4 vdd vss de4i de4 INVx10
XVde5 vdd vss de5i de5 INVx10
XVde6 vdd vss de6i de6 INVx10
XVde7 vdd vss de7i de7 INVx10
XVde8 vdd vss de8i de8 INVx10
XVde9 vdd vss de9i de9 INVx10
XVde10 vdd vss de10i de10 INVx10
XVde11 vdd vss de11i de11 INVx10
XVde12 vdd vss de12i de12 INVx10
XVde13 vdd vss de13i de13 INVx10
XVde14 vdd vss de14i de14 INVx10
XVde15 vdd vss de15i de15 INVx10

****************************************************************************
* Implementation of the Encoder block, that generates the check bits (c0, ..., c15)
* from the received information bits (de0, ..., de15).
****************************************************************************
XENCODER0 vdd vss de0 de1 de2 de3 c0 XORCB
XENCODER1 vdd vss de4 de5 de6 de7 c1 XORCB
XENCODER2 vdd vss de8 de9 de10 de11 c2 XORCB
XENCODER3 vdd vss de12 de13 de14 de15 c3 XORCB
XENCODER4 vdd vss de0 de4 de8 de12 c4 XORCB
XENCODER5 vdd vss de1 de5 de9 de13 c5 XORCB
XENCODER6 vdd vss de2 de6 de10 de14 c6 XORCB
XENCODER7 vdd vss de3 de7 de11 de15 c7 XORCB
XENCODER8 vdd vss de0 de5 de10 de15 c8 XORCB
XENCODER9 vdd vss de1 de4 de11 de14 c9 XORCB
XENCODER10 vdd vss de2 de7 de8 de13 c10 XORCB
XENCODER11 vdd vss de3 de6 de9 de12 c11 XORCB
XENCODER12 vdd vss de0 de6 de11 de13 c12 XORCB
XENCODER13 vdd vss de1 de7 de10 de12 c13 XORCB
XENCODER14 vdd vss de2 de4 de9 de15 c14 XORCB
XENCODER15 vdd vss de3 de5 de8 de14 c15 XORCB


****************************************************************************
* Generation of information bits read from the cache (d0, ..., d15), that together with
* check bits (c0, ..., c15) are given as inputs to the Decoder block.
* These bits have been obtained by inverting signals (d0i, ..., d15i) gerenated by ideal
* voltage sources, so that these signal present realistic waveforms.
****************************************************************************
*Information bits read from cache (d0, ..., d15)
XVd0 vdd vss d0i d0 INVx10
XVd1 vdd vss d1i d1 INVx10
XVd2 vdd vss d2i d2 INVx10
XVd3 vdd vss d3i d3 INVx10
XVd4 vdd vss d4i d4 INVx10
XVd5 vdd vss d5i d5 INVx10
XVd6 vdd vss d6i d6 INVx10
XVd7 vdd vss d7i d7 INVx10
XVd8 vdd vss d8i d8 INVx10
XVd9 vdd vss d9i d9 INVx10
XVd10 vdd vss d10i d10 INVx10
XVd11 vdd vss d11i d11 INVx10
XVd12 vdd vss d12i d12 INVx10
XVd13 vdd vss d13i d13 INVx10
XVd14 vdd vss d14i d14 INVx10
XVd15 vdd vss d15i d15 INVx10



****************************************************************************
* Implementation of the Decoder block.
* It receives words read from the cache(d0, ..., d15, c0, ..., c15), and generates as outputs:
* - the corrected informationthe bits (dcorr0, ..., dcorr15)
* - the error signal ErrorDet = 1 in case a single or double error is corrected.
*****************************************************************************
* Implementation of the Syndrome Generator sub-block of the decoder
* Regenerated check bits are (cx0, ..., cx15)
XENCODERx0 vdd vss d0 d1 d2 d3 cx0 XORCB
XENCODERx1 vdd vss d4 d5 d6 d7 cx1 XORCB
XENCODERx2 vdd vss d8 d9 d10 d11 cx2 XORCB
XENCODERx3 vdd vss d12 d13 d14 de15 cx3 XORCB
XENCODERx4 vdd vss d0 d4 d8 d12 cx4 XORCB
XENCODERx5 vdd vss d1 d5 d9 d13 cx5 XORCB
XENCODERx6 vdd vss d2 d6 d10 d14 cx6 XORCB
XENCODERx7 vdd vss d3 d7 d11 d15 cx7 XORCB
XENCODERx8 vdd vss d0 d5 d10 d15 cx8 XORCB
XENCODERx9 vdd vss d1 d4 d11 d14 cx9 XORCB
XENCODERx10 vdd vss d2 d7 d8 d13 cx10 XORCB
XENCODERx11 vdd vss d3 d6 d9 d12 cx11 XORCB
XENCODERx12 vdd vss d0 d6 d11 d13 cx12 XORCB
XENCODERx13 vdd vss d1 d7 d10 d12 cx13 XORCB
XENCODERx14 vdd vss d2 d4 d9 d15 cx14 XORCB
XENCODERx15 vdd vss d3 d5 d8 d14 cx15 XORCB

*If (cx0, ..., cx15)=(c0, ..., c15) then (s0, ..., s15)=(0, ..., 0) so no error.
XCOMPARATOR0 vdd vss cx0 c0 s0 XOR
XCOMPARATOR1 vdd vss cx1 c1 s1 XOR
XCOMPARATOR2 vdd vss cx2 c2 s2 XOR
XCOMPARATOR3 vdd vss cx3 c3 s3 XOR
XCOMPARATOR4 vdd vss cx4 c4 s4 XOR
XCOMPARATOR5 vdd vss cx5 c5 s5 XOR
XCOMPARATOR6 vdd vss cx6 c6 s6 XOR
XCOMPARATOR7 vdd vss cx7 c7 s7 XOR
XCOMPARATOR8 vdd vss cx8 c8 s8 XOR
XCOMPARATOR9 vdd vss cx9 c9 s9 XOR
XCOMPARATOR10 vdd vss cx10 c10 s10 XOR
XCOMPARATOR11 vdd vss cx11 c11 s11 XOR
XCOMPARATOR12 vdd vss cx12 c12 s12 XOR
XCOMPARATOR13 vdd vss cx13 c13 s13 XOR
XCOMPARATOR14 vdd vss cx14 c14 s14 XOR
XCOMPARATOR15 vdd vss cx15 c15 s15 XOR

* Implementation of the Syndrome Decoder sub-block of the decoder
*error vector (dx1, ..., dx15)
XMAJVOT0 vdd vss s0 s4 s8 s12 dx0 MAJVOT
XMAJVOT1 vdd vss s0 s5 s9 s13 dx1 MAJVOT
XMAJVOT2 vdd vss s0 s6 s10 s14 dx2 MAJVOT
XMAJVOT3 vdd vss s2 s7 s11 s15 dx3 MAJVOT
XMAJVOT4 vdd vss s1 s4 s9 s14 dx4 MAJVOT
XMAJVOT5 vdd vss s1 s5 s8 s15 dx5 MAJVOT
XMAJVOT6 vdd vss s1 s6 s11 s12 dx6 MAJVOT
XMAJVOT7 vdd vss s1 s7 s10 s13 dx7 MAJVOT
XMAJVOT8 vdd vss s2 s4 s10 s15 dx8 MAJVOT
XMAJVOT9 vdd vss s2 s5 s11 s14 dx9 MAJVOT
XMAJVOT10 vdd vss s2 s6 s8 s13 dx10 MAJVOT
XMAJVOT11 vdd vss s2 s7 s9 s12 dx11 MAJVOT
XMAJVOT12 vdd vss s3 s4 s11 s13 dx12 MAJVOT
XMAJVOT13 vdd vss s3 s5 s10 s12 dx13 MAJVOT
XMAJVOT14 vdd vss s3 s6 s9 s15 dx14 MAJVOT
XMAJVOT15 vdd vss s3 s7 s8 s14 dx15 MAJVOT

* Implementation of the Corrector sub-block of the decoder
* corrected outputs (dcorr1, ..., dcorr15)
XCORRECTION0 vdd vss d0 dx0 dcorr0 XOR
XCORRECTION1 vdd vss d1 dx1 dcorr1 XOR
XCORRECTION2 vdd vss d2 dx2 dcorr2 XOR
XCORRECTION3 vdd vss d3 dx3 dcorr3 XOR
XCORRECTION4 vdd vss d4 dx4 dcorr4 XOR
XCORRECTION5 vdd vss d5 dx5 dcorr5 XOR
XCORRECTION6 vdd vss d6 dx6 dcorr6 XOR
XCORRECTION7 vdd vss d7 dx7 dcorr7 XOR
XCORRECTION8 vdd vss d8 dx8 dcorr8 XOR
XCORRECTION9 vdd vss d9 dx9 dcorr9 XOR
XCORRECTION10 vdd vss d10 dx10 dcorr10 XOR
XCORRECTION11 vdd vss d11 dx11 dcorr11 XOR
XCORRECTION12 vdd vss d12 dx12 dcorr12 XOR
XCORRECTION13 vdd vss d13 dx13 dcorr13 XOR
XCORRECTION14 vdd vss d14 dx14 dcorr14 XOR
XCORRECTION15 vdd vss d15 dx15 dcorr15 XOR

* Implementation of the error generation sub-block of the decoder
XErr_Det vdd 0 S0 S1 S2 S3 S4 S5 S6 S7 S8 S9 S10 S11 S12 S13 S14 S15 ErrorDet ErrDet


* Examples of possible BFs affecting the Decoer (all commented) that can be
* used to verify the ability of our monitoring scheme to detect faults
* affecting the Decoder blcock.
*Rbf0 dcorr0 d0n 100
*Rbf1 dcorr1 d1n 100
*Rbf2 dcorr2 d2n 100
*Rbf3 dcorr3 d3n 100
*Rbf4 dcorr4 d4n 100
*Rbf5 dcorr5 d5n 100
*Rbf6 dcorr6 d6n 100
*Rbf7 dcorr7 d7n 100
*Rbf8 dcorr8 d8n 100
*Rbf9 dcorr9 d9n 100
*Rbf10 dcorr10 d10n 100
*Rbf11 dcorr11 d11n 100
*Rbf12 dcorr12 d12n 100
*Rbf13 dcorr13 d13n 100
*Rbf14 dcorr14 d14n 100
*Rbf15 dcorr15 d15n 100


****************************************************************************
* Implementation of the Fault Detector (FDetector) block.
*
* FDetector receives the words read from the cache (d0, ..., d15, c0, ..., c15) and
* the corrected informationthe bits at the outputs of the Decoder (dcorr0, ..., dcorr15).
*
* FDetector generates as output the signals (EC1, EC2).
*
* FDetector makes (EC1, EC2) = (0, 1) or (1, 0) if the information bits read from the cache
* are equal to the Decoder outputs and if the check bits read from the cache are correct.
* Otherwise, FDetector makes (EC1, EC2) = (0, 0) or (1, 1).
*
* In order to detect faults affecting the Decoder, Signals (EC1, EC2) should be
* analyzed together with the error signal ErrorDet generated by the Decoder:
*
* For a fault-free Decoder, it is
* (EC1, EC2, ErrorDet) = (0, 0, 1) or (1, 1, 1), or
* (EC1, EC2, ErrorDet) = (0, 1, 0) or (1, 0, 0).
*
* In case of faults affecting the Decoder, it results:
* (EC1, EC2, ErrorDet) = (0, 1, 1) or (1, 0, 1), or
* (EC1, EC2, ErrorDet) = (0, 0, 0) or (1, 1, 0).
****************************************************************************

* Generation of the complement of the word read from the cache (d0n, ..., d15n, cx0n,..., cx15n).
* They are needed since the FDetector uses a TRC to compare:
* - the information bits read from the cache with the outputs of the Decoder
* - the check bits read from the cache with internally regenerated check bits (from the
*   information bits read from the cache.
XVd0n vdd vss d0 d0n INVx10
XVd1n vdd vss d1 d1n INVx10
XVd2n vdd vss d2 d2n INVx10
XVd3n vdd vss d3 d3n INVx10
XVd4n vdd vss d4 d4n INVx10
XVd5n vdd vss d5 d5n INVx10
XVd6n vdd vss d6 d6n INVx10
XVd7n vdd vss d7 d7n INVx10
XVd8n vdd vss d8 d8n INVx10
XVd9n vdd vss d9 d9n INVx10
XVd10n vdd vss d10 d10n INVx10
XV11dn vdd vss d11 d11n INVx10
XVd12n vdd vss d12 d12n INVx10
XVd13n vdd vss d13 d13n INVx10
XVd14n vdd vss d14 d14n INVx10
XVd15n vdd vss d15 d15n INVx10

XVcx0n vdd vss cx0 cx0n INVx10
XVcx1n vdd vss cx1 cx1n INVx10
XVcx2n vdd vss cx2 cx2n INVx10
XVcx3n vdd vss cx3 cx3n INVx10
XVcx4n vdd vss cx4 cx4n INVx10
XVcx5n vdd vss cx5 cx5n INVx10
XVcx6n vdd vss cx6 cx6n INVx10
XVcx7n vdd vss cx7 cx7n INVx10
XVcx8n vdd vss cx8 cx8n INVx10
XVcx9n vdd vss cx9 cx9n INVx10
XVcx10n vdd vss cx10 c10n INVx10
XVcx11n vdd vss cx11 cx11n INVx10
XVcx12n vdd vss cx12 cx12n INVx10
XVcx13n vdd vss cx13 cx13n INVx10
XVcx14n vdd vss cx14 cx14n INVx10
XVcx15n vdd vss cx15 cx15n INVx10

* Implementation of an Encoder to regenerate the check bits (cx0R, ..., cx15R)
* from the information bits read from the cache.
XENCODERx0R vdd vss d0 d1 d2 d3 c0R XORCB
XENCODERx1R vdd vss d4 d5 d6 d7 c1R XORCB
XENCODERx2R vdd vss d8 d9 d10 d11 c2R XORCB
XENCODERx3R vdd vss d12 d13 d14 d15 c3R XORCB
XENCODERx4R vdd vss d0 d4 d8 d12 c4R XORCB
XENCODERx5R vdd vss d1 d5 d9 d13 c5R XORCB
XENCODERx6R vdd vss d2 d6 d10 d14 c6R XORCB
XENCODERx7R vdd vss d3 d7 d11 d15 c7R XORCB
XENCODERx8R vdd vss d0 d5 d10 d15 c8R XORCB
XENCODERx9R vdd vss d1 d4 d11 d14 c9R XORCB
XENCODERx10R vdd vss d2 d7 d8 d13 c10R XORCB
XENCODERx11R vdd vss d3 d6 d9 d12 c11R XORCB
XENCODERx12R vdd vss d0 d6 d11 d13 c12R XORCB
XENCODERx13R vdd vss d1 d7 d10 d12 c13R XORCB
XENCODERx14R vdd vss d2 d4 d9 d15 c14R XORCB
XENCODERx15R vdd vss d3 d5 d8 d14 c15R XORCB

* Implementation of a 32-variable TRC that:
* - compares the complement of the information bits read from the cache
*   (d0n, ..., d15n) with the Decoder outputs (dcorr0, ..., dcorr15), and the
*   complement of the check bits read from the cache (cx0n, ..., cx15n) with the
*   regenerated check bits (cx0R,..., cx15R).
* - generates the outputs (EC1, EC2) of the FDetector.
X1TRC8FDet vdd vss d0n dcorr0 d1n dcorr1 d2n dcorr2 d3n dcorr3 d4n dcorr4 d5n dcorr5 d6n dcorr6 d7n dcorr7 out1TrcFDet1 out2TrcFDet1 TRC8
X2TRC8FDet vdd vss d8n dcorr8 d9n dcorr9 d10n dcorr10 d11n dcorr11 d12n dcorr12 d13n dcorr13 d14n dcorr14 d15n dcorr15 out1TrcFDet2 out2TrcFDet2 TRC8
X3TRC8FDet vdd vss cx0n c0R cx1n c1R cx2n c2R cx3n c3R cx4n c4R cx5n c5R cx6n c6R cx7n c7R out1TrcFDet3 out2TrcFDet3 TRC8
X4TRC8FDet vdd vss cx8n c8R cx9n c9R cx10n c10R cx11n c11R cx12n c12R cx13n c13R cx14n c14R cx15n c15R out1TrcFDet4 out2TrcFDet4 TRC8
X5TRC4FDet vdd vss out1TrcFDet1 out2TrcFDet1 out1TrcFDet2 out2TrcFDet2 out1TrcFDet3 out2TrcFDet3 out1TrcFDet4 out2TrcFDet4 EC1 EC2 TRC4



****************************************************************************
* Implementation of the Aging Detector (ADetector) block.
*
* The ADetector monitors the outputs of the Decoder (dcorr0, ..., dcorr15)
* during a proper timing guardband, in order to detect late transitions
* of Decoder outputs due to BTI.
*
* ADetector receives the outputs of the Decoder (dcorr0, ..., dcorr15), and a
* Time Window Control signal (TWC), which is asserted only during the timing guardband.
* TWC enables to activte ADetector only during the timing gurband.
*
* ADetector generates two signals (AC1, AC2) encoded by the two rail code.
*
* When TWC=0, ADetector is disabled and makes (AC1, AC2) = (0,1) or (1,0).
*
* When TWC=1, ADetector is enabled to detect late transitions of Decoder outputs:
* - If all the Decoder outputs are stable while TWC=1, our ADetector makes
*   (AC1, AC2) = (0,1) or (1,0).
* - If at least one Decoder output presents a transition when TWC=1, our ADetector generates
*   an error message, thus it makes makes (AC1, AC2) = (0,0) or (1,1).
****************************************************************************

* Implementation of Transition Detector, by recalling subcircuit TD (one per Decoer output),
* to detect late  transitions on (dcorr0, ..., dcorr15) when TWC=1.
XTD_1 vdd vss dcorr0 TWC TWCn o1_1 o2_1 TD
XTD_2 vdd vss dcorr1 TWC TWCn o1_2 o2_2 TD
XTD_3 vdd vss dcorr2 TWC TWCn o1_3 o2_3 TD
XTD_4 vdd vss dcorr3 TWC TWCn o1_4 o2_4 TD
XTD_5 vdd vss dcorr4 TWC TWCn o1_5 o2_5 TD
XTD_6 vdd vss dcorr5 TWC TWCn o1_6 o2_6 TD
XTD_7 vdd vss dcorr6 TWC TWCn o1_7 o2_7 TD
XTD_8 vdd vss dcorr7 TWC TWCn o1_8 o2_8 TD
XTD_9 vdd vss dcorr8 TWC TWCn o1_9 o2_9 TD
XTD_10 vdd vss dcorr9 TWC TWCn o1_10 o2_10 TD
XTD_11 vdd vss dcorr10 TWC TWCn o1_11 o2_11 TD
XTD_12 vdd vss dcorr11 TWC TWCn o1_12 o2_12 TD
XTD_13 vdd vss dcorr12 TWC TWCn o1_13 o2_13 TD
XTD_14 vdd vss dcorr13 TWC TWCn o1_14 o2_14 TD
XTD_15 vdd vss dcorr14 TWC TWCn o1_15 o2_15 TD
XTD_16 vdd vss dcorr15 TWC TWCn o1_16 o2_16 TD

* Implementation of the 16-variable Two-Rail Code (TRC) checker that receives the outputs of
* the 16 transition detectors and generates the outputs of our ADetector (AC1, AC2).

XTRC8_1 vdd vss o1_1 o2_1 o1_2 o2_2 o1_3 o2_3 o1_4 o2_4 o1_5 o2_5 o1_6 o2_6 o1_7 o2_7 o1_8 o2_8 out1Trc1 out2Trc1 TRC8
XTRC8_2 vdd vss o1_9 o2_9 o1_10 o2_10 o1_11 o2_11 o1_12 o2_12 o1_13 o2_13 o1_14 o2_14 o1_15 o2_15 o1_16 o2_16 out1Trc2 out2Trc2 TRC8
XTRC2_1 vdd vss out1Trc1 out2Trc1 out1Trc2 out2Trc2 AC1 AC2 TRC2


*********************************************************************
* Voltage Sources
*********************************************************************

V_Vdd vdd 0 0.8V
V_Vss vss 0 0V


*Clock signals
V_clk clk vss PULSE (0V 0.8V 0ps 'trise' 'tfall' 'clk/2' 'clk')
V_clkn clkn vss PULSE (0.8V 0V 0ps 'trise' 'tfall' 'clk/2' 'clk')

*Time Window Control signals
V_TWC TWC vss PULSE (0V 0.8V 'clk-tm' 'trise' 'tfall' 'tm-{tdelaynot}' 'clk')
V_TWCn TWCn vss PULSE (0.8V 0V 'clk-tm' 'trise' 'tfall' 'tm-{tdelaynot}' 'clk')

*Reset signals
*V_ResN Res vss PWL (0ps 0V '3*clk+clk/4' 0V '(3*clk+clk/4)+trise' 0.8V '(3*clk+clk/4)+trise+200ps' 0.8V '(3*clk+clk/4)+trise+200ps+tfall' 0V)
*V_Res ResN vss PWL (0ps 0.8V '3*clk+clk/4' 0.8V '(3*clk+clk/4)+trise' 0V '(3*clk+clk/4)+trise+200ps' 0V '(3*clk+clk/4)+trise+200ps+tfall' 0.8V)



****************************************************************************
* Generation of signals for the generation of information bits,
* that should be stored on the cache, and that are given as inputs to the Encoder block.
* As an example, we considered (d0, ..., d15) = (0,1,1,0,1,0,1,1,0,1,0,0,0,1,0,1)
* The related check bits are (c0, ..., c15) = (0,1,1,0,1,1,0,0,1,0,1,0,0,0,0,0)
*****************************************************************************
V_de0i de0i vss 0.8V
V_de1i de1i vss 0V
V_de2i de2i vss 0V
V_de3i de3i vss 0.8V
V_de4i de4i vss 0V
V_de5i de5i vss 0.8V
V_de6i de6i vss 0V
V_de7i de7i vss 0V
V_de8i de8i vss 0.8V
V_de9i de9i vss 0V
V_de10i de10i vss 0.8V
V_de11i de11i vss 0.8V
V_de12i de12i vss 0.8V
V_de13i de13i vss 0V
V_de14i de14i vss 0.8V
V_de15i de15i vss 0V




****************************************************************************
* Generation of information bits read from the cache (d0, ..., d15), that together with
* check bits (c0, ..., c15) are given as inputs to the Decoder block.
* Example of fault-free case:
* (d0, ..., d15) = (0,1,1,0,1,0,1,1,0,1,0,0,0,1,0,1)
* (c0, ..., c15) = (0,1,1,0,1,1,0,0,1,0,1,0,0,0,0,0)
****************************************************************************

*For inputs d0i and d4i, we include two generators, to emulate the case in which
*the bits are correct and one to emulate the case in which they are erroneous.

*Uncoment the following generator to emulate the presence of an error on d0i after 0.5ns
*V_d0i d0i vss PULSE (0V 0.8V 0ps 'trise' 'tfall' '(clk-tm-30ps)/2' 'clk-tm-30ps')

*Coment the following generator to emulate the presence of an error on d0i
V_d0i d0i vss 0.8V

V_d1i d1i vss 0V
V_d2i d2i vss 0V
V_d3i d3i vss 0.8V

*Uncoment the following generator to emulate the presence of an error on d4i after 0.5ns
V_d4i d4i vss PULSE (0V 0.8V 0.4ns 'trise' 'tfall' '5*clk' '10*clk')

*Coment the following generator to emulate the presence of an error on d4i
*V_d4i d4i vss 0V

V_d5i d5i vss 0.8V
V_d6i d6i vss 0V
V_d7i d7i vss 0V
V_d8i d8i vss 0.8V
V_d9i d9i vss 0V
V_d10i d10i vss 0.8V
V_d11i d11i vss 0.8V
V_d12i d12i vss 0.8V
V_d13i d13i vss 0V
V_d14i d14i vss 0.8V
V_d15i d15i vss 0V


